The number of players Manchester United want to sign this summer transfer window has emerged. Man United only signed two players, Bruno Fernandes and Odion Ighalo in the January transfer window from Sporting Lisbon and Shanghai Greenland Shenhua, respectively. According to the Manchester Evening News, Man United manager, Ole Gunnar Solskjaer wants the club to prioritize three signings, a midfielder, forward and striker at the end of the season. Solskjaer is eager to bolster his squad this summer with midfielder, Paul Pogba, expected to leave Old Trafford and forwards, Marcus Rashford and Anthony Martial currently need support in the Red Devils’ attack. Solskjaer’s side is presently in the 8th position in the Premier League table with 35 points from 25 games. Man United will take on Chelsea in their next Premier League fixture on Monday.